==Old English==
===Etymology===
From [[neah|nēah]] + [[gebur|ġebūr]].  Corresponding to Old Saxon [[nahbur|nāhbūr]] (Dutch [[nabuur]]), Old High German [[nahgibur|nāhgibūr]] (German [[Nachbar]]), Old Norse [[nábúi]] (Swedish [[nabo]]).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'næ:ahje.bu:r/

===Noun===
'''nēahġebūr''' ''m''
# a [[neighbour]]

